In ExternalComment Bean, we need to have a new constructor(existing can be modified ) which handles this situation.

It is observed that the comments and worklogs which are restricted, they are not handled in JIM.

    @JsonCreator
	public ExternalComment(@JsonProperty("body") String body, @JsonProperty("author") @Nullable String author, @JsonProperty("created") @Nullable DateTime created,
			@JsonProperty("groupLevel") @Nullable String groupLevel, @JsonProperty("roleLevel") @Nullable String roleLevel) {
		this.body = body;
		this.author = author;
		this.created = created;
		this.groupLevel = groupLevel;
		this.roleLevel = roleLevel;
	}

Same thing should be done in ExternalWorklog Bean.

Also, this should be handled in ExternalUtils where actual comment gets created.

this.commentManager.create(issue, authorKey, authorKey, externalComment.getBody(), null, null, timePerformed, timePerformed, dispatchEvent, tweakIssueUpdateDate);

Here  grouplevel and rolelevel  info. should be passed instead of null,null

