Currently, background reindexes are single threaded and the customer does not have a way to change the number of threads for that operation to a multi-threaded process.

Ideally, the customer would be able to configure the number of threads for a background reindex  (depending on their hardware specifications) by configuring a parameter or property in JIRA or a JVM argument as is done in Confluence. 
The default value could be 1 thread and the customer would be able to increase it to a specifix max value.

h3.  Issue Summary

When a user goes to a dashboard and selects the {{...}} to *create a Sub-Task*, the screen provided to the user though showing up as the create Sub Task screen contains the wrong issue type.

Also, when the user selects the option *Create Linked Issues*, nothing happens.

This issue is reproducible in a vanilla JIRA instance and has been tested on JIRA 7.2.7, 7.3.1, 7.3.0.

h3. Steps to reproduce
{panel:title=Create Subtask}
# Create a test dashboard and add any gadget that allows you to modify an issue directly from it like the _assigned to me_ or _Filter Result_.
# Create an issue and assign it to yourself (_assuming we are using assigned to me gadget_).
# Go to the dashboard.
# Press the *{{...}}*
# Select Create Sub-Task.
{panel}

{panel:title=Create Linked Issues}
# From the same same gadget.
# Press {{...}}
# Select Create Linked Issues.
{panel}

h3. Expected Result
{panel:title=Create Subtask}
JIRA would show the Create subtask screen which should contain the correct issue types in the issue type field.
{panel}

{panel:title=Create Linked Issues}
JIRA would be expected to show the create linked issue screen.
{panel}

h3. Actual Result
{panel:title=Create Subtask}
JIRA would show the create issue screen but instead of the expected issue types in the issue type field, it would be showing those for the regular Create issue screen.
{panel}

{panel:title=Create Linked Issues}
Nothing happens.

