In the class com.atlassian.cache.Cache<K,V> the documentation for the method getKeys() is
{code:java}
    /**
     * Gets the keys of all objects currently stored in the cache. This will return the keys in a new collection.
     * @return a collection of {@link Object}s keys
     */
    @Nonnull
    Collection<K> getKeys();
{code}

This gives the understanding that it gives a new collection which can be mutated. However looking at the backing implementation in the InMemory DelegatingCache I notice
{code:java}
    @Nonnull
    public Collection<K> getKeys() {
        try {
            return this.internalCache.asMap().keySet();
        } catch (Exception var2) {
            throw new CacheException(var2);
        }
    }
{code}

And the keySet() in Java clearly states that "The set is backed by the map, so changes to the map are reflected in the set, and vice-versa". 
In other words mutation of the collection received by the getKeys will change the map in the cache. 

Implementation of the method needs to be fixed.

